# Use Parameter Knowledge Base

When creating or significantly modifying a Remotion composition, you MUST consult
the structured parameter documentation in `docs/` to ensure motion, visual, and
temporal parameters are correct for the target style profile.

---

## Step 1 — Identify the Style Profile

Determine which profile the composition targets. Ask the user if unclear.

| Profile | File | Key feel |
|---------|------|----------|
| Snappy SaaS | `docs/profiles/snappy-saas.md` | Apple-clean, critically damped, fast cuts |
| Luxury Slow | `docs/profiles/luxury-slow.md` | Warm, organic, longer holds |
| Kinetic Typography | `docs/profiles/kinetic-typography.md` | Text-dominant, word slams |
| Dark Tech | `docs/profiles/dark-tech.md` | Dark bg, glow accents, ambient |
| Product Showcase | `docs/profiles/product-showcase.md` | UI demos, dashboards, phone reveals |

Read the full profile file. Use its L1–L5 parameter tables as your starting
defaults for spring configs, colors, font sizes, scene durations, etc.

---

